    "narrative": "The Zebras are positioned for a high-ceiling offensive output today, anchored by Christian Yelich and Yordan Alvarez, who offer the day\u2019s premier projections at 75.84 and 75.09, respectively. Yelich benefits significantly from a favorable park factor and a strong dynamic platoon advantage, while Alvarez exploits a soft matchup against Feltner. Trea Turner and Kyle Schwarber also emerge as critical anchors in the top third of the order; their aggressive utilization against Houser creates a high-probability stack for runs and stolen base potential, essential for maintaining our 5x5 Roto efficiency.\n\nCaution is advised regarding our lower-order contributors, particularly Hyeseong Kim and Pete Crow-Armstrong, both of whom carry sub-50 projections and face negative modifiers due to their lineup placement and unfavorable pitcher skill sets. While Victor Scott II remains a viable play for speed, the wind conditions at the sites for Keith, Yelich, and Schwarber warrant close monitoring; the \"Wind In\" penalty slightly dampens the power expectations for those sluggers. We are keeping a sharp eye on these margins, as maximizing plate appearances from the high-score cohort remains our priority to gain ground in the standings.",
